Backend API

This is the backend API for our application, which provides the necessary endpoints to interact with the database. It is built with Node.js and uses SQLite as its database.

## Endpoints ##
-----------------------------------------------------------
### POST /register
-----------------------------------------------------------

Registers a new user to the database.

#### Request body:

json

{
    "email": "<user-email>",
    "password": "<user-password>"
}

-----------------------------------------------------------
### POST /login
-----------------------------------------------------------

Verifies the user credentials.

#### Request body:

json

{
    "email": "<user-email>",
    "password": "<user-password>"
}

-----------------------------------------------------------
### POST /add-comment
-----------------------------------------------------------

Adds a new comment to a file.

#### Request body:

json

{
    "file": "<file-id>",
    "user": "<user-id>",
    "str": "<comment>"
}

-----------------------------------------------------------
### POST /upload-file
-----------------------------------------------------------

Uploads a new file to the database.

#### Request body:

json

{
    "email": "<user-email>",
    "password": "<user-password>",
    "owner": "<owner-id>"
}

#### Request files:

json

{
    "file": "<file-data>"
}

-----------------------------------------------------------
### GET /files/:timestamp
-----------------------------------------------------------

Downloads a file with the given timestamp.

#### Parameters:

- `timestamp` - the timestamp of the file to be downloaded

## Setup

To use this API, please follow these steps:

1. Clone this repository.
2. Install dependencies using `npm install`.
3. Run the server using `node server.js`.

## Database

The database is located at `../db/db.db`. Please make sure it exists before using the API.